# QA Coverage Upgrade — Missing Business Logic Tests

Gap analysis identified 7 critical business logic modules with zero unit test coverage. All new tests follow the established architecture (`tests/unit/`, Jest + mocks).

## Coverage Gap Summary

| Module | Risk | Current Coverage | Gap |
|--------|------|-----------------|-----|
| `feeCalculator.ts` | 🔴 Financial | None | Discount math, guards, edge cases |
| `mcqParser.ts` | 🔴 Data integrity | None | Parsing, validation, malformed input |
| Auth registration API | 🔴 Security | None | Field validation, duplicate check, username gen |
| OTP verification API | 🔴 Security | None | Expiry, attempts, rate limiting |
| Expense API | 🟡 Financial | None | Soft-delete, lock guards, root-only |
| Fee record creation | 🔴 Financial | None | calcFees integration, duplicate prevention |
| Attendance locking | 🟡 Data integrity | None | Lock/unlock, rejection on locked records |

## Proposed Changes

### Unit Tests — Pure Business Logic (no DB required)

#### [NEW] [feeCalculator.test.ts](file:///media/swastik/focus/ldm%20feb/tests/unit/lib/feeCalculator.test.ts)
- Percentage discount calculation (10%, 50%, 100%)
- Flat discount calculation
- Flat discount capped at base price
- Percentage takes priority over flat
- Zero discount (no discount applied)
- Negative base price throws
- Discount percent out of range (< 0, > 100) throws
- Zero base price edge case

#### [NEW] [mcqParser.test.ts](file:///media/swastik/focus/ldm%20feb/tests/unit/lib/mcqParser.test.ts)
- Valid MCQ block parsing (standard format)
- Multiple question formats (Q1., 1., Q 1.)
- Option format variants (A), A., (A), a))
- Answer format variants (Answer:, Ans:, Correct:)
- Missing answer line → error
- Less than 4 options → error
- Duplicate question dedup
- Empty input → error
- Malformed block → skipped with error
- Short block (< 3 lines) → error

### Unit Tests — API Route Logic (mocked DB)

#### [NEW] [register.test.ts](file:///media/swastik/focus/ldm%20feb/tests/unit/api/auth/register.test.ts)
- Missing required fields → 400
- Duplicate email → 409
- Username collision auto-increment
- Successful registration → 201

#### [NEW] [verifyOtp.test.ts](file:///media/swastik/focus/ldm%20feb/tests/unit/api/auth/verifyOtp.test.ts)
- Missing email/OTP → 400
- No OTP record found → 404
- Already verified → 400
- Expired OTP → 410
- Max attempts exceeded → 429
- Wrong OTP increments attempts → 401
- Correct OTP → verified

#### [NEW] [expenses.test.ts](file:///media/swastik/focus/ldm%20feb/tests/unit/api/finance/expenses.test.ts)
- Non-admin access → 401
- Missing required fields → 400
- Amount ≤ 0 → 400
- Soft-delete: non-root user → 403
- Soft-delete: locked record → 403
- Soft-delete: already deleted → 400
- Soft-delete: success with audit log

#### [NEW] [feeRecords.test.ts](file:///media/swastik/focus/ldm%20feb/tests/unit/api/finance/feeRecords.test.ts)
- Non-admin access → 401
- Missing required fields → 400
- Negative base price → 400
- Student not found → 404
- Duplicate fee record → 409
- Successful creation with calcFees math

#### [NEW] [attendance.test.ts](file:///media/swastik/focus/ldm%20feb/tests/unit/api/attendance/attendance.test.ts)
- markAttendance: locked record → rejected
- markAttendance: new record → created
- markAttendance: existing record → updated
- updateStudentAttendance: locked → rejected
- updateStudentAttendance: not found → error
- lockAttendance: lock + unlock operations

## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests

```bash
# Run only new tests
./node_modules/.bin/jest tests/unit/lib/feeCalculator.test.ts --config jest.config.ts --forceExit
./node_modules/.bin/jest tests/unit/lib/mcqParser.test.ts --config jest.config.ts --forceExit

# Run all unit tests (new + existing)
SUPPRESS_JEST_WARNINGS=true ./node_modules/.bin/jest --config jest.config.ts --forceExit

# Confirm no existing tests broken
# Expected: All 4 existing + 7 new = 11+ test suites, all passing
```

> [!IMPORTANT]
> Pure logic tests (`feeCalculator`, `mcqParser`) need zero mocking — they test exported functions directly. API route tests require mocking `next-auth`, `mongoose`, `bcryptjs`, and `next/cache`.
